>> title: Lemon Garlic Chicken with Tomatoes

1. Prepare the chicken: Season @chicken breasts{2} generously with salt and pepper on both sides.

1. Cook the chicken: Heat 1 tablespoon @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add @chicken breasts{2} and cook 6-7 minutes per side until golden brown and cooked through (internal temperature 165°F). Remove from pan and set aside.

1. Sauté aromatics: In the same pan, add remaining @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Add sliced onions and cook 3-4 minutes until softened. Add minced garlic and cook another 30 seconds until fragrant.

1. Add @tomatoes{2}: Add diced tomatoes to the pan and cook 3-5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they start to break down and release their juices.

1. Finish the sauce: Add @lemon{1} juice and let simmer 2-3 minutes. Season with @Salt and pepper to taste{}.

1. Combine and serve: Return chicken to the pan to warm through and coat with sauce. Garnish with fresh @Optional: herbs{} if desired.

## Notes

- The @tomatoes{2} will create a light, fresh sauce as they cook down

- Don’t overcook the garlic to avoid bitterness

- Serve over rice, pasta, or with crusty bread to enjoy the sauce

- Can be garnished with fresh parsley, thyme, or oregano

## Cook Time

- Prep: 10 minutes

- Cook: 20 minutes

- Total: 30 minutes
